{|ia|o1h1n|at|}|HT|n|at|^j@2^Y@3Here is another example. You open 1H and partner bids 1NT. Partner has neither 3 hearts (would have raised to 2H) nor 4 spades (would have bid 1S). Partner has no more than two hearts, and does not have four spades. Again, just file that information away, as it may be useful later.|HT|r|at|^B@2^Y@3The only exception would be if you are playing forcing 1N and partner has a 3-card limit raise. In that case, it is possible for partner to have three hearts (but not 4 spades). You will find out on his next bid if that is the case, but provisionally you can assume he does not have 3-card heart support.|
