HT|V|at|^B@2{|ia|o1c1h1n|at|}|HT|u|at|^j@2^Y@3In the example on the left, since the rebid was neither 1S nor 2H, partner has at most three spades and three hearts. Partner also has at least 4 clubs--if he/she only had three clubs, the hand must contain four diamonds, and therefore 1D would have been the opening bid. Look at all the information that can be gleaned from such a common auction!|
